timeline.bodyText:
I'd call this STRIMZI_CATEGORY. I'm also not sure this is really the correct class to declare it on. Though I can't think of a better one. Looking at our CRD-annotated classes, such as Kafka, we have various constants which are common across numerous classes:
public static final String CRD_API_VERSION = "apiextensions.k8s.io/v1beta1";
public static final String RESOURCE_GROUP = "kafka.strimzi.io";
But I'm not sure even that's enough to warrant some CrdConstants class. Thoughts @scholzj ?

